HEADWORD: Acquisitive
<hw>Ac*quis"i*tive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Acquired.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He died not in his <qex>acquisitive</qex>, but in his native
soil.</q> <rj><qau>Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Able or disposed to make acquisitions; acquiring;
<as>as, an <ex>acquisitive</ex> person or disposition</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acquisitively</ent>⟦br⟧
